World number one Roger Federer revelled in his perfect start to the year after improving to 15-0 in 2018 following his victory at the Indian Wells Masters.Federer's flawless year continued thanks to his 7-5 6-4 victory over Jeremy Chardy en route to the quarter-finals on Wednesday. The 20-time grand slam winner and defending champion was too good against Chardy as he reached the last eight without dropping a set at the ATP 1000 tournament.Hyeon Chung is next up in a repeat of the Australian Open semi-final, which Federer won following the South Korean's retirement due to blist ers in January.And if Federer can see off Chung, the Swiss superstar will match his previous best start to a season when the 36-year-old went 16-0 in 2006.